b_tor_vacuum_1.documentation: Characteristics of the vacuum toroidal field. time assumed to be one level above

b_tor_vacuum_1.r0.documentation: Reference major radius where the vacuum toroidal magnetic field is given (usually a fixed position such as the middle of the vessel at the equatorial midplane)

b_tor_vacuum_1.r0_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "r0"

b_tor_vacuum_1.b0_error_index.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "b0"

b_tor_vacuum_1.b0.documentation: Vacuum toroidal field at R0 [T]; Positive sign means anti-clockwise when viewed from above. The product R0B0 must be consistent with the b_tor_vacuum_r field of the tf IDS.
